I believe that selecting 'none' for the workflow scheme will force all issues in the project to default back to the default read-only workflow. If that is the case, it seems like it would be more appropriate to have a default read-only workflow scheme, that assigns all issues to the default workflow. Then instead of 'none' you would have a choice of 'Default System Workflow Scheme' and the other custom schemes. Otherwise it's confusing because workflows can't be assigned to projects, only workflow schemes can be assigned to projects.

The BIG problem here is that if I select 'none' for a project. The project doesn't show up on the 'Workflow Schemes' page. So I'm not aware that a workflow scheme has not been assigned. So either a default workflow scheme needs to be created, or projects with no workflow scheme should appear on the 'Workflow Schemes' page some other way.

